  "body": "### Component\n\nFoundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n# Enable robust and secure CI/CD processes by creating a separate `foundryup`\r\n\r\nChanges like this: https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/5361 where `-L` is removed should be communicated to the user, maybe adding a depreciation notice first.\r\n\r\nExample solution:\r\n\r\n## Change release and linkage of the new script\r\n\r\n<https://github.com/sambacha/foundryup-tests>\r\n\r\nThis workflow runs and creates the foundryup file as a release asset, versus the current fetching of the script via `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/`. Arguably this is preferable as it's both a known release version as opposed to the current way of just grabbing the latest file over raw.githubusercontent.com \r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\n> Note that the asset `v-2023-07-17` is in fact just a `.tar.gz` archive\r\n\r\n```console\r\ncurl -sSL https://github.com/sambacha/foundryup-tests/releases/download/tag-2023-07-17/v-2023-07-17 | tar -v -C $HOME/ -xz\r\nx foundryup/\r\nx foundryup/install\r\nx foundryup/.gitkeep\r\n```\r\nInspecting `refs/heads/master` we can see the hash\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ git ls-remote https://github.com/sambacha/foundryup-tests master -h\r\n✔︎ 9c5b8d411c456212957efbf4fcaf8002e78d15bc\trefs/heads/master\r\nx 74f3b97370de8748651421a95a4e3e05d45239fb\trefs/tags/master\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat hash matches the value defined in `SCRIPT_COMMIT_SHA` \r\n \r\n```bash\r\n# runs with Makefile to generate hash on CI\r\n# shellcheck disable=SC2034\r\nSCRIPT_COMMIT_SHA=\"9c5b8d411c456212957efbf4fcaf8002e78d15bc\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"612\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-07-17 at 1 42 47 AM\" src=\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/32783916/fb7f4921-8618-4fb5-9359-21700a1f4655\">\r\n\r\n",
